article.description: — Miryne Thomas had a season-high 20 points as Ball State rolled past Northern Illinois 78-58 on Saturday.
article.headline: Thomas scores 20 to lead Ball St. over N. Illinois 78-58
article.linkText: Thomas scores 20 to lead Ball St. over N. Illinois 78-58
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- — Miryne Thomas had a season-high 20 points as Ball State rolled past Northern Illinois 78-58 on Saturday. Luke Bumbalough had 11 points for Ball State (6-5, 4-2 Mid-American Conference). Blake Huggins added 10 points. K.J. Walton had 10 points and six rebounds. Zool Kueth had 15 points for the Huskies (2-10, 1-6). Trendon Hankerson added 12 points. Darius Beane had eight rebounds and seven assists. The Cardinals improve to 2-0 against the Huskies this season. Ball State defeated Northern Illinois 79-70 on Dec. 8. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
